    <briefdescription>
<para>PWM driver class implemented according to C++ singleton design pattern. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The PWM driver class handles the the generation of pulse width modulated signals. It uses the public zephyr API for the PWM driver. See details in <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/apidoc/latest/group__pwm__interface.html">API documentation</ulink> and for details of the <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/hardware/peripherals/adc.html">PWM configuration in the devicetree</ulink><linebreak/>
The PWM driver class provides an init method, methods to set PWM period and pulse width and methods to update PWM HW from settings, to start and to stop PWM generation. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
